juniIsisMIB.name: juniIsisMIB

revisions.description: Modifiled width of juniIsisMplsTeTunnelName from 32 to 40
Added juniIsisSysReferenceBandwidth and juniIsisSysHighReferenceBandwidth to juniIsisSysEntry
Added juniIsisSysMplsTeSpfUseAnyBestPath to juniIsisSysEntry. Added juniIsisMplsTeTunnelTable to juniIsisSystemGroup
Default value for juniIsisSysLSPIgnoreErrors is changed from false to true. Default value for juniIsisCircMeshGroup =1 is removed
L2 Buffer Size is added and is made obsolete.
Updated the SystemID TEXTUAL-CONVENTION to be inline with standard - SystemID should now be exactly 6 bytes. - SystemID description modified. All zeros are invalid.
Updated the upper bound for Max Split Paths and removed the L2 Buffer Size
Modified the default value for the juniIsisSysSetOverloadBitStartupDuration object. This object has a meaning only if the ISIS overload bit is set.
Updated the upper bound for Authentication Key Id in Area Authentication, Domain Authentication, L1 Circuit and L2 Circuit Tables.
Changed the lower bound value & default value of juniIsisSysSetOverloadBitStartupDuration from 0 to 5.
Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names.
Added support for simple password protection.
Initial version of this MIB module, based on draft-ietf-isis-wg-mib.

juniIsisMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniIsisMIB.description: The intermediate system to intermediate system (IS-IS) routing protocol MIB for Juniper Networks E-series products. This MIB provides objects for management of the IS-IS Routing protocol, as described in ISO 10589, when it is used to construct routing tables for IP networks, as described in RFC 1195.

OSINSAddress.name: OSINSAddress
OSINSAddress.description: OSI Network Service Address, e.g. NSAP, Network Entity Title

SystemID.name: SystemID
SystemID.description: A system ID of exactly six bytes. Must not be all zeros.

OperState.name: OperState
OperState.description: Type used in enabling and disabling a row.

AuthTime.name: AuthTime
AuthTime.description: Then number of seconds since Jan. 1 1970.

LSPBuffSize.name: LSPBuffSize
LSPBuffSize.description: Integer sub range for LSP size.

SupportedProtocol.name: SupportedProtocol
SupportedProtocol.description: Types of network protocol supported by Integrated ISIS. The values for ISO8473 and IP are those registered for these protocols in ISO TR9577.

JuniDefaultMetric.name: JuniDefaultMetric
JuniDefaultMetric.description: Integer sub-range for default metric for single hop. The value is truncated to 63 when the juniIsisSysL1MetricStyle or juniIsisSysL2MetricStyle is set to juniIsisMetricStyleNarrow

OtherMetric.name: OtherMetric
OtherMetric.description: Integer sub-range for metrics other than the default metric for single hop.

juniIsisSysTable.name: juniIsisSysTable
juniIsisSysTable.description: The set of instances of the Integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system.

juniIsisSysEntry.name: juniIsisSysEntry
juniIsisSysEntry.description: Each row defines information specific to a single instance of the protocol existing on the system.

juniIsisSysInstance.name: juniIsisSysInstance
juniIsisSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

juniIsisSysVersion.name: juniIsisSysVersion
juniIsisSysVersion.description: The version number of the IS-IS protocol to which this instance conforms. This value must be set by the implementation when the row is valid.

juniIsisSysType.name: juniIsisSysType
juniIsisSysType.description: The type of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

juniIsisSysID.name: juniIsisSysID
juniIsisSysID.description: The ID for this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This value is appended to each of the instance's area addresses to form the Network Entity Titles valid for this instance. The derivation of a value for this object is implementation-specific. Some implementations may assign values and not permit write MAX-ACCESS, others may require the value to be set manually.

juniIsisSysMaxPathSplits.name: juniIsisSysMaxPathSplits
juniIsisSysMaxPathSplits.description: Maximum number of paths with equal routing metric value which it is permitted to split between. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

juniIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt.name: juniIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt
juniIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt.description: Maximum interval, in seconds, between generated LSPs by this instance. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

juniIsisSysOrigLSPBuffSize.name: juniIsisSysOrigLSPBuffSize
juniIsisSysOrigLSPBuffSize.description: The maximum size of LSPs and SNPs originated by this instance. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

juniIsisSysMaxAreaAddresses.name: juniIsisSysMaxAreaAddresses
juniIsisSysMaxAreaAddresses.description: The maximum number of area addresses to be permitted for the area in which this instance exists. Note that all Intermediate Systems in the same area must have the same value configured for this attribute if correct operation is to be assumed. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

juniIsisSysMinL1LSPGenInt.name: juniIsisSysMinL1LSPGenInt
juniIsisSysMinL1LSPGenInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between successive generation of L1 LSPs with the same LSPID by this instance. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

juniIsisSysMinL2LSPGenInt.name: juniIsisSysMinL2LSPGenInt
juniIsisSysMinL2LSPGenInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between successive generation of L2 LSPs with the same LSPID by this instance. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

juniIsisSysPollESHelloRate.name: juniIsisSysPollESHelloRate
juniIsisSysPollESHelloRate.description: The value, in seconds, to be used for the suggested ES configuration timer in ISH PDUs when soliciting the ES configuration.

juniIsisSysWaitTime.name: juniIsisSysWaitTime
juniIsisSysWaitTime.description: Number of seconds to delay in waiting state before entering on state. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

juniIsisSysOperState.name: juniIsisSysOperState
juniIsisSysOperState.description: The operational state of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. Setting this object to the value on when its current value is off enables operation of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol.

juniIsisSysL1State.name: juniIsisSysL1State
juniIsisSysL1State.description: The state of the Level 1 database.

juniIsisSysLSPL1DbaseOloads.name: juniIsisSysLSPL1DbaseOloads
juniIsisSysLSPL1DbaseOloads.description: Number of times the LSP L1 database has become overloaded.

juniIsisSysManAddrDropFromAreas.name: juniIsisSysManAddrDropFromAreas
juniIsisSysManAddrDropFromAreas.description: Number of times a manual address has been dropped from the area.

juniIsisSysAttmptToExMaxSeqNums.name: juniIsisSysAttmptToExMaxSeqNums
juniIsisSysAttmptToExMaxSeqNums.description: Number of times the IS has attempted to exceed the maximum sequence number.

juniIsisSysSeqNumSkips.name: juniIsisSysSeqNumSkips
juniIsisSysSeqNumSkips.description: Number of times a sequence number skip has occurred.

juniIsisSysOwnLSPPurges.name: juniIsisSysOwnLSPPurges
juniIsisSysOwnLSPPurges.description: Number of times a zero-aged copy of the system's own LSP is received from some other node.

juniIsisSysIDFieldLenMismatches.name: juniIsisSysIDFieldLenMismatches
juniIsisSysIDFieldLenMismatches.description: Number of times a PDU is received with a different value for ID field length to that of the receiving system.

juniIsisSysMaxAreaAddrMismatches.name: juniIsisSysMaxAreaAddrMismatches
juniIsisSysMaxAreaAddrMismatches.description: Number of times a PDU is received with a different value for MaximumAreaAddresses from that of the receiving system.

juniIsisSysOrigL2LSPBuffSize.name: juniIsisSysOrigL2LSPBuffSize
juniIsisSysOrigL2LSPBuffSize.description: The maximum size of Level 2 LSPs and SNPs originated by this system. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

juniIsisSysL2State.name: juniIsisSysL2State
juniIsisSysL2State.description: The state of the Level 2 database.

juniIsisSysLSPL2DbaseOloads.name: juniIsisSysLSPL2DbaseOloads
juniIsisSysLSPL2DbaseOloads.description: Number of times the Level 2 LSP database has become overloaded.

juniIsisSysAuthFails.name: juniIsisSysAuthFails
juniIsisSysAuthFails.description: The number of authentication failures recognized by this instance of the protocol.

juniIsisSysLSPIgnoreErrors.name: juniIsisSysLSPIgnoreErrors
juniIsisSysLSPIgnoreErrors.description: If true, allow the router to ignore IS-IS link state packets (LSPs) that are received with internal checksum errors rather than purging the LSPs.

juniIsisSysMaxAreaCheck.name: juniIsisSysMaxAreaCheck
juniIsisSysMaxAreaCheck.description: When on, enables checking of maximum area addresses per IS version of ISO10589.

juniIsisSysSetOverloadBitStartupDuration.name: juniIsisSysSetOverloadBitStartupDuration
juniIsisSysSetOverloadBitStartupDuration.description: Specifies the length in time of seconds to set the overload bit from startup. This object must be set together with juniIsisSysSetOverloadBit, otherwise the agent will return zero. Zero value for this object implies that the overload bit is not set. Zero value does not have any meaning for this object.

juniIsisSysMaxLspLifetime.name: juniIsisSysMaxLspLifetime
juniIsisSysMaxLspLifetime.description: Specifies the maximum time (in seconds) a LSP will remain in the box without being refreshed before being considered invalid.

juniIsisSysL1SpfInterval.name: juniIsisSysL1SpfInterval
juniIsisSysL1SpfInterval.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between level 1 SPF calculations.

juniIsisSysL2SpfInterval.name: juniIsisSysL2SpfInterval
juniIsisSysL2SpfInterval.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between level 2 SPF calculations.

juniIsisSysIshHoldTime.name: juniIsisSysIshHoldTime
juniIsisSysIshHoldTime.description: Specify a holdtime advertised in ESH/ISH PDUs.

juniIsisSysIshConfigTimer.name: juniIsisSysIshConfigTimer
juniIsisSysIshConfigTimer.description: Specify the rate of transmission for ESH and ISH packets.

juniIsisSysDistributeDomainWide.name: juniIsisSysDistributeDomainWide
juniIsisSysDistributeDomainWide.description: When on, enables distribution of prefixes throughout a multi-level domain.

juniIsisSysDistance.name: juniIsisSysDistance
juniIsisSysDistance.description: The weight applied to IS-IS routes.

juniIsisSysL1MetricStyle.name: juniIsisSysL1MetricStyle
juniIsisSysL1MetricStyle.description: Specifies the type of IP reachability TLV to advertise in level 1 LSPs.

juniIsisSysL2MetricStyle.name: juniIsisSysL2MetricStyle
juniIsisSysL2MetricStyle.description: Specifies the type of IP reachability TLV to advertise in level 2 LSPs.

juniIsisSysMplsTeLevel.name: juniIsisSysMplsTeLevel
juniIsisSysMplsTeLevel.description: Select flooding of MPLS traffic engineering link information into the specified ISIS level.

juniIsisSysMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex.name: juniIsisSysMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex
juniIsisSysMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex.description: Configure the stable router interface ID to designate it as TE capable. A value of zero is used to remove any configured router interface ID.

juniIsisSysMplsTeSpfUseAnyBestPath.name: juniIsisSysMplsTeSpfUseAnyBestPath
juniIsisSysMplsTeSpfUseAnyBestPath.description: Configure whether or not to consider spf paths when alternate tunnel path exists

juniIsisSysReferenceBandwidth.name: juniIsisSysReferenceBandwidth
juniIsisSysReferenceBandwidth.description: Configure the reference bandwitdth used to calculate the link cost in bits per second.If the reference bandwidth is greater than the maximum value reportable by this object then this object should report its maximum value (4,294,967,295) and juniIsisSysHighReferenceBandwidth must be used to report the reference bandwidth.

juniIsisSysHighReferenceBandwidth.name: juniIsisSysHighReferenceBandwidth
juniIsisSysHighReferenceBandwidth.description: Configure the reference bandwitdth in mega bits per second. It is used to calculate the link cost.

juniIsisManAreaAddrTable.name: juniIsisManAreaAddrTable
juniIsisManAreaAddrTable.description: The set of manual area addresses configured on this Intermediate System.

juniIsisManAreaAddrEntry.name: juniIsisManAreaAddrEntry
juniIsisManAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one area address manually configured on this system.

juniIsisManAreaAddrSysInstance.name: juniIsisManAreaAddrSysInstance
juniIsisManAreaAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

juniIsisManAreaAddr.name: juniIsisManAreaAddr
juniIsisManAreaAddr.description: A manually configured area address for this system. This object follows the index behaviour. Note: an index for the entry {1, {49.0001} active} in this table would be the ordered pair (1, (0x03 0x49 0x00 0x01)), as the length of an octet string is part of the OID.

juniIsisManAreaAddrRowStatus.name: juniIsisManAreaAddrRowStatus
juniIsisManAreaAddrRowStatus.description: The state of the juniIsisManAreaAddrEntry. This object follows the RowStatus behaviour. If an attempt is made to set this object to the value off when the corresponding juniIsisManAreaAddrEntry is the only valid entry for this instance and when the corresponding IS-IS instance has juniIsisSysOperState set to on then the attempt is rejected.

juniIsisSysProtSuppTable.name: juniIsisSysProtSuppTable
juniIsisSysProtSuppTable.description: This table contains the manually configured set of protocols supported by each instance of the Integrated ISIS protocol.

juniIsisSysProtSuppEntry.name: juniIsisSysProtSuppEntry
juniIsisSysProtSuppEntry.description: Each entry contains one protocol supported by an instance of the Integrated ISIS protocol.

juniIsisSysProtSuppSysInstance.name: juniIsisSysProtSuppSysInstance
juniIsisSysProtSuppSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

juniIsisSysProtSuppProtocol.name: juniIsisSysProtSuppProtocol
juniIsisSysProtSuppProtocol.description: One supported protocol. This object follows the index behaviour.

juniIsisSysProtSuppRowStatus.name: juniIsisSysProtSuppRowStatus
juniIsisSysProtSuppRowStatus.description: The state of the juniIsisSysProtSuppEntry. This object follows the RowStatus behavior.

juniIsisSummAddrTable.name: juniIsisSummAddrTable
juniIsisSummAddrTable.description: The set of IP summary addresses to use in forming the contents of Level 2 LSPs originated by this level 2 Intermediate System.

juniIsisSummAddrEntry.name: juniIsisSummAddrEntry
juniIsisSummAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP summary address.

juniIsisSummAddrSysInstance.name: juniIsisSummAddrSysInstance
juniIsisSummAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviours.

juniIsisSummAddress.name: juniIsisSummAddress
juniIsisSummAddress.description: The IP Address value for this summary address. This object follows the index behaviour.

juniIsisSummAddrMask.name: juniIsisSummAddrMask
juniIsisSummAddrMask.description: The mask value for this summary address. This object follows the index behaviour.

juniIsisSummAddrRowStatus.name: juniIsisSummAddrRowStatus
juniIsisSummAddrRowStatus.description: The existence state of this summary address. This object follows the RowStatus behaviour.

juniIsisSummAddrOperState.name: juniIsisSummAddrOperState
juniIsisSummAddrOperState.description: The operational state of this entry. This object follows the operationalState behaviour. When the operational state changes if this would cause the contents of LSPs originated by the system to change then those new LSPs must be generated and sent as soon as is permitted by the ISIS protocol.

juniIsisSummAddrDefaultMetric.name: juniIsisSummAddrDefaultMetric
juniIsisSummAddrDefaultMetric.description: The default metric value to announce this summary address with in Level 1 or 2 LSPs generated by this system. A Metric value of 0 indicates to use the lowest metric value amongst the routes being summarized. When advertising a metric value into a narrow domain (juniIsisSysL1MetricStyle or juniIsisSysL2MetricStyle is set to juniIsisMetricStyleNarrow) the value will be truncated to 63.

juniIsisSummAddrDelayMetric.name: juniIsisSummAddrDelayMetric
juniIsisSummAddrDelayMetric.description: The delay metric value to announce this summary address with in Level 2 LSPs generated by this system. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

juniIsisSummAddrExpenseMetric.name: juniIsisSummAddrExpenseMetric
juniIsisSummAddrExpenseMetric.description: The expense metric value to announce this summary address with in Level 2 LSPs generated by this system. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

juniIsisSummAddrErrorMetric.name: juniIsisSummAddrErrorMetric
juniIsisSummAddrErrorMetric.description: The error metric value to announce this summary address with in Level n LSPs generated by this system. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

juniIsisSummLevel.name: juniIsisSummLevel
juniIsisSummLevel.description: The level of database at which to annouce this summary.

juniIsisCircTable.name: juniIsisCircTable
juniIsisCircTable.description: The table of circuits used by each instance of Integrated IS-IS on this system.

juniIsisCircEntry.name: juniIsisCircEntry
juniIsisCircEntry.description: An juniIsisCircEntry exists for each circuit used by Integrated IS-IS on this system.

juniIsisCircSysInstance.name: juniIsisCircSysInstance
juniIsisCircSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

juniIsisCircIfIndex.name: juniIsisCircIfIndex
juniIsisCircIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex for the interface to which this circuit corresponds.

juniIsisCircLocalID.name: juniIsisCircLocalID
juniIsisCircLocalID.description: An identification that can be used in protocol packets to identify a circuit. Implementations may devise ways to assure that this value is suitable for the circuit it is used on. LAN packets only have space for 8 bits. Values of juniIsisCircLocalID do not need to be unique. They are only required to differ on LANs where the Intermediate System is the Designated Intermediate System.

juniIsisCircOperState.name: juniIsisCircOperState
juniIsisCircOperState.description: The operational state of the circuit. This object follows the operationalState behaviour.

juniIsisCircRowStatus.name: juniIsisCircRowStatus
juniIsisCircRowStatus.description: The existence state of this circuit. This object follows the RowStatus behaviour.

juniIsisCircType.name: juniIsisCircType
juniIsisCircType.description: The type of the circuit. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour. The type specified must be compatible with the type of the interface defined by the value of juniIsisCircIfIndex.

juniIsisCircL1DefaultMetric.name: juniIsisCircL1DefaultMetric
juniIsisCircL1DefaultMetric.description: The default metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic.

juniIsisCircL1DelayMetric.name: juniIsisCircL1DelayMetric
juniIsisCircL1DelayMetric.description: The delay metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

juniIsisCircL1ExpenseMetric.name: juniIsisCircL1ExpenseMetric
juniIsisCircL1ExpenseMetric.description: The expense metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

juniIsisCircL1ErrorMetric.name: juniIsisCircL1ErrorMetric
juniIsisCircL1ErrorMetric.description: The error metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

juniIsisCircExtDomain.name: juniIsisCircExtDomain
juniIsisCircExtDomain.description: If true, suppress normal transmission of and interpretation of Intra-domain ISIS PDUs on this circuit.

juniIsisCircAdjChanges.name: juniIsisCircAdjChanges
juniIsisCircAdjChanges.description: The number of times an adjacency state change has occurred on this circuit.

juniIsisCircInitFails.name: juniIsisCircInitFails
juniIsisCircInitFails.description: The number of times initialization of this circuit has failed.

juniIsisCircRejAdjs.name: juniIsisCircRejAdjs
juniIsisCircRejAdjs.description: The number of times an adjacency has been rejected on this circuit.

juniIsisCircOutCtrlPDUs.name: juniIsisCircOutCtrlPDUs
juniIsisCircOutCtrlPDUs.description: The number of IS-IS control PDUs sent on this circuit.

juniIsisCircInCtrlPDUs.name: juniIsisCircInCtrlPDUs
juniIsisCircInCtrlPDUs.description: The number of IS-IS control PDUs received on this circuit.

juniIsisCircIDFieldLenMismatches.name: juniIsisCircIDFieldLenMismatches
juniIsisCircIDFieldLenMismatches.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with an ID field length different to that for this system has been received.

juniIsisCircL2DefaultMetric.name: juniIsisCircL2DefaultMetric
juniIsisCircL2DefaultMetric.description: The default metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic.

juniIsisCircL2DelayMetric.name: juniIsisCircL2DelayMetric
juniIsisCircL2DelayMetric.description: The delay metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

juniIsisCircL2ExpenseMetric.name: juniIsisCircL2ExpenseMetric
juniIsisCircL2ExpenseMetric.description: The expense metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

juniIsisCircL2ErrorMetric.name: juniIsisCircL2ErrorMetric
juniIsisCircL2ErrorMetric.description: The error metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

juniIsisCircManL2Only.name: juniIsisCircManL2Only
juniIsisCircManL2Only.description: When true, indicates that this circuit is to be used only for level 2. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

juniIsisCircL1ISPriority.name: juniIsisCircL1ISPriority
juniIsisCircL1ISPriority.description: The priority for becoming LAN Level 1 Deignated Intermediate System on a broadcast circuit.

juniIsisCircL1CircID.name: juniIsisCircL1CircID
juniIsisCircL1CircID.description: The LAN ID allocated by the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System. Where this system is not aware of the value (because it is not participating in the Level 1 Designated Intermediate System election), this object has the value which would be proposed for this circuit (i.e. the concatenation of the local system ID and the one octet local Circuit ID for this circuit.

juniIsisCircL1DesIS.name: juniIsisCircL1DesIS
juniIsisCircL1DesIS.description: The ID of the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System on this circuit. If, for any reason this system is not partaking in the relevant Designated Intermediate System election process, then the value returned is the zero length OCTET STRING.

juniIsisCircLANL1DesISChanges.name: juniIsisCircLANL1DesISChanges
juniIsisCircLANL1DesISChanges.description: The number of times the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System has changed.

juniIsisCircL2ISPriority.name: juniIsisCircL2ISPriority
juniIsisCircL2ISPriority.description: The priority for becoming LAN level 2 Designated Intermediate System.

juniIsisCircL2CircID.name: juniIsisCircL2CircID
juniIsisCircL2CircID.description: The LAN ID allocated by the LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System. Where this system is not aware of this value (because it is not participating in the Level 2 Designated Intermediate System election), this object has the value which would be proposed for this circuit (i.e. the concatenation of the local system ID and the one octet local Circuit ID for this circuit.

juniIsisCircL2DesIS.name: juniIsisCircL2DesIS
juniIsisCircL2DesIS.description: The ID of the LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System on this circuit. If, for any reason, this system is not partaking in the relevant Designated Intermediate System election process, then the value returned is the zero length OCTET STRING.

juniIsisCircLANL2DesISChanges.name: juniIsisCircLANL2DesISChanges
juniIsisCircLANL2DesISChanges.description: The number of times the LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System has changed.

juniIsisCircMCAddr.name: juniIsisCircMCAddr
juniIsisCircMCAddr.description: Specifies which type of multicast address will be used for sending HELLO PDUs on this circuit.

juniIsisCircPtToPtCircID.name: juniIsisCircPtToPtCircID
juniIsisCircPtToPtCircID.description: The ID of the circuit allocated during initialization. If no value has been negotiated (either because the adjacency is to an End System, or because initialization has not yet successfully completed), this object has the value which would be proposed for this circuit (i.e. the concatenation of the local system ID and the one octet local Circuit ID for this circuit.

juniIsisCircL1HelloTimer.name: juniIsisCircL1HelloTimer
juniIsisCircL1HelloTimer.description: Maximum period, in seconds, between Level 1 IIH PDUs on multiaccess networks. It is also used as the period between Hellos on point to point circuits. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

juniIsisCircL2HelloTimer.name: juniIsisCircL2HelloTimer
juniIsisCircL2HelloTimer.description: Maximum period, in seconds, between Level 1 IIH PDUs on multiaccess networks. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

juniIsisCircL1HelloMultiplier.name: juniIsisCircL1HelloMultiplier
juniIsisCircL1HelloMultiplier.description: This value is multiplied by the corresponding HelloTimer and the result in seconds (rounded up) is used as the holding time in transmitted hellos, to be used by receivers of hello packets from this IS.

juniIsisCircL2HelloMultiplier.name: juniIsisCircL2HelloMultiplier
juniIsisCircL2HelloMultiplier.description: This value is multiplied by the corresponding HelloTimer and the result in seconds (rounded up) is used as the holding time in transmitted hellos, to be used by receivers of hello packets from this IS

juniIsisCircMinLSPTransInt.name: juniIsisCircMinLSPTransInt
juniIsisCircMinLSPTransInt.description: Minimum interval, in milliseconds, between transmission of LSPs on a circuit. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour. This timer shall be capable of a resolution not coarser than 10 milliseconds.

juniIsisCircMinLSPReTransInt.name: juniIsisCircMinLSPReTransInt
juniIsisCircMinLSPReTransInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between re-transmission of an Level 1 or 2 LSP. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

juniIsisCircL1CSNPInterval.name: juniIsisCircL1CSNPInterval
juniIsisCircL1CSNPInterval.description: Interval of time, in seconds, between transmission of Level 1 CSNPs on multiaccess networks if this router is the designated router. On point-to-point networks the default is to not transmit CSNPs. Hence CSNP interval will be 0 for point-to-point networks.

juniIsisCircL2CSNPInterval.name: juniIsisCircL2CSNPInterval
juniIsisCircL2CSNPInterval.description: Interval of time, in seconds, between transmission of Level 2 CSNPs on multiaccess networks if this router is the designated router. On point-to-point networks the default is to not transmit CSNPs. Hence CSNP interval will be 0 for point-to-point networks.

juniIsisCircLSPThrottle.name: juniIsisCircLSPThrottle
juniIsisCircLSPThrottle.description: Minimal interval of time, in milliseconds, between retransmissions of LSPs on a point to point interface.

juniIsisCircMeshGroupEnabled.name: juniIsisCircMeshGroupEnabled
juniIsisCircMeshGroupEnabled.description: Is this port a member of a mesh group, or blocked? Circuits in the same mesh group act as a virtual multiaccess network. LSPs seen on one circuit in a mesh group will not be flooded to another circuit in the same mesh group.

juniIsisCircMeshGroup.name: juniIsisCircMeshGroup
juniIsisCircMeshGroup.description: Circuits in the same mesh group act as a virtual multiaccess network. LSPs seen on one circuit in a mesh group will not be flooded to another circuit in the same mesh group. If juniIsisCircMeshGroupEnabled is false, this value is ignored. Default value returned as 0 has no significance for this variable.

juniIsisCircLevel.name: juniIsisCircLevel
juniIsisCircLevel.description: The type of this circuit. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

juniIsisCircState.name: juniIsisCircState
